12/11/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Greece has been removed from the list of countries cited by the United States for failing to curb human trafficking. 
Foreign Ministry General Secretary for International Economic Relations Dimitris Dollis announced the news Tuesday (11 November), after meetings in Washington. 
He says the US State Department has noted positive steps in fighting trafficking.
In other news, Greek Defence Minister Yiannos Papantoniou rejected the possibility of compulsory military service for women. 
He insisted service by women would remain voluntary. 
(Kathimerini, AFP - 11/11/03)
